    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-04-15T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-04-15T11:00:00-05:00" n="301"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d301">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">830/4–1554: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative at the United Nations</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lodge</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d301fn1">Repeated to Brussels as telegram 1030, Apr. 15
                        (330/4–1554).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-04-15T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 15, 1954—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>628. Re <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> elections. In light of comment in
                    Brussels 777, April 13, I think we should now be very careful to avoid
                    indicating to anyone that we might support Belgium for the <gloss
                        target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>. On contrary, I think we should give very urgent
                    consideration to possibility of building up the candidacy of a non-European
                    country that we can be sure will <pb facs="0559" n="531" xml:id="pg_531"/>
                    support us on the Chinese representation issue as well as other issues in the
                        <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>. I think both Thailand and the Philippines
                    might be very good possibilities. Neither has ever been a member of the <gloss
                        target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>, both strongly support us and we want them to
                    play their full part in developing plans for a unified action program in
                    Southeast Asia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lodge</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
